function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(first(word)), words)
end
```

The function `keep_only_names` takes a list of strings (`words`) as an argument. It applies the built-in Julia method `filter` to this list, which returns a new list consisting only of elements for which the provided function (`isuppercase(first(word))`) is true. The function `isuppercase` checks if the first character of the string is uppercase, and `first` gets the first (and in this case only) character of the string.
